<section class="about-section" id="about" aria-labelledby="about-heading">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 id="about-heading" class="section-title">About HackMI</h2>
    <p class="section-subtitle">A Michigan hackathon for builders, students, and curious technologists.</p>
    <div class="about-card glass">
      <p class="about-lead">
        HackMI is a weekend-long innovation sprint in <strong>Detroit</strong>, bringing together public participants and
        students from schools like the <strong>University of Michigan</strong> and <strong>Wayne State University</strong>.
        Teams ship creative projects that blend software, design, and real-world impact—with room to experiment boldly.
      </p>
      <p class="about-body">
        Whether you are polishing an agentic workflow, crafting a polished UI, or exploring hardware-adjacent ideas, HackMI is
        built to give you mentorship, momentum, and a memorable community experience in the heart of the Detroit tech corridor.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

